SIMPLE: skyscraper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skyscraper
<hw>Sky"scrap`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sd>(a)</sd>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> (1) <def>A skysail of a triangular form.</def>
<mark>[Rare]</mark> (2) <def>A name for the one of the fancy sails
alleged to have been sometimes set above the skysail.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A very tall building, especially
one over 20 stories high.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Hence, anything
usually large, high, or excessive.</def> <mark>[Slang or
Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skyward</ent>⟦br⟧
